<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="no"?>
<!--
    FS25_PropertyBorders Translation Template
    ==========================================
    
    HOW TO ADD YOUR LANGUAGE:
    
    1. Copy this file and rename it to l10n_XX.xml where XX is your language code.
       Supported codes (matching FS25 game languages):
         br = Brazilian Portuguese    cs = Czech             ct = Chinese Traditional
         cz = Czech (alt)             da = Danish            de = German
         ea = Spanish (Latin America) en = English           es = Spanish
         fc = French Canadian         fi = Finnish           fr = French
         hu = Hungarian               id = Indonesian        it = Italian
         jp = Japanese                kr = Korean            nl = Dutch
         no = Norwegian               pl = Polish            pt = Portuguese
         ro = Romanian                ru = Russian           sv = Swedish
         tr = Turkish                 uk = Ukrainian         vi = Vietnamese
    
    2. Translate every text="" value below to your language.
       Do NOT change the name="" attributes — they are code keys.
    
    3. Preserve format specifiers exactly as-is:
         %d   = integer number (e.g., farmland count)
         %s   = string (e.g., a name, or a pre-formatted number)
    
       NOTE ON NUMBER FORMATTING (i18n):
         Decimal and thousands separators vary by locale (e.g., 1,000.5 vs 1.000,5).
         The mod uses g_i18n:formatNumber() to format all player-facing numbers
         BEFORE inserting them into translated strings. This means height values
         arrive as pre-formatted strings via %s, not raw floats. You do NOT need
         to worry about decimal separators in your translation — just place %s
         where the number should appear.
    
    4. Place your completed file in the l10n/ folder alongside the existing files.
       The game will automatically detect and use it when the player's language matches.
    
    5. (Optional) Submit your translation as a pull request or send it to the mod author!
    
    IMPORTANT:
    - File encoding MUST be UTF-8.
    - Do not add or remove <text> entries — the code expects all keys to exist.
    - If you are unsure about a translation, leave the English value; the game
      falls back to English for any missing keys.
-->
